cit:title.gco:CharacterString: Spatial data: A large-scale database of modeled contemporary and future water temperature data for 10,774 Michigan, Minnesota and Wisconsin Lakes

cit:otherCitationDetails.gco:CharacterString: Winslow, L.A., Hansen, G.J.A., and Read, J.S., 2017, Data release: A large-scale database of modeled contemporary and future water temperature data for 10,774 Michigan, Minnesota and Wisconsin Lakes: U.S. Geological Survey, http://dx.doi.org/10.5066/F7DV1H10.

mri:abstract.gco:CharacterString: Climate change has been shown to influence lake temperatures globally. To better understand the diversity of lake responses to climate change and give managers tools to manage individual lakes, we modelled daily water temperature profiles for 10,774 lakes in Michigan, Minnesota and Wisconsin for contemporary (1979-2015) and future (2020-2040 and 2080-2100) time periods with climate models based on the Representative Concentration Pathway 8.5, the worst-case emission scenario.

mri:purpose.gco:CharacterString: Fisheries biology, limnological research, and climate science.
